      "content": "i was walking around lower manhattan last night and looking at some old maps. have u ever noticed how the way certain buildings are angled doesn't actually follow the street grid? like it feels deliberate. almost like they're pointing at specific coordinates if you overlay them right. i'm starting to think the urban layout isn't just about traffic or zoning.",
